## Cons-specific lemmas (List only, no direct Array counterpart)

These lemmas use `cons`/`::` which doesn't have a direct Array analogue:

- `take_cons`, `drop_cons`: pattern-match on cons
- `drop_eq_getElem_cons`: `drop i l = l[i] :: drop (i + 1) l`
- `drop_length_cons`: `(a :: l).drop l.length = [l.getLast h]`
- `set_eq_take_append_cons_drop`: `l.set i a = l.take i ++ a :: l.drop (i + 1)`
- `take_concat_get`: `(l.take i).concat l[i] = l.take (i+1)`

## Tail-specific lemmas (List only)

- `drop_one`: `l.drop 1 = l.tail`
- `drop_add_one_eq_tail_drop`: `l.drop (i + 1) = (l.drop i).tail`
- `tail_drop`: `(l.drop i).tail = l.drop (i + 1)`
- `drop_tail`: `l.tail.drop i = l.drop (i + 1)`

## Nil-specific lemmas (List only, trivially `#[]` for Array)

- `drop_eq_nil_of_eq_nil`, `ne_nil_of_drop_ne_nil`
- `take_eq_nil_of_eq_nil`, `ne_nil_of_take_ne_nil`
